### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@customerId1 = c1
@customerId2 = c2
@productId1 = p1
@productId2 = p2
@coupon10 = DESCUENTO10
@couponFixed100 = PRIMERACOMPRA

###############################################
# Checkout - Finalizar Compras
# Tests: 78-103
###############################################

### 78. Error - Checkout de Carrito Vacío
# Intentar hacer checkout con el carrito vacío de c1 (si lo limpiamos antes)
# Primero asegurarnos de que c1 está vacío
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cart/remove-product HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}",
  "productId": "{{productId1}}"
}

###

### 79. Verificar c1 vacío
GET {{baseUrl}}/cart/{{customerId1}} HTTP/1.1

###

### 80. Error - Checkout de Carrito Vacío (debe fallar)
# Esperado: error "Cannot checkout an empty cart"
POST {{baseUrl}}/checkout HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}"
}

###

### 81. Preparar carrito c1 para checkout exitoso
# Agregar 2 Laptops (p1) y 1 Mouse (p2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart/add-product HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}",
  "productId": "{{productId1}}"
}

###

### 82. Agregar segunda Laptop a c1
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart/add-product HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}",
  "productId": "{{productId1}}"
}

###

### 83. Agregar Mouse a c1
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart/add-product HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}",
  "productId": "{{productId2}}"
}

###

### 84. Aplicar cupón 10% a c1 antes del checkout
POST {{baseUrl}}/cart/apply-coupon HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}",
  "couponCode": "{{coupon10}}"
}

###

### 85. Ver carrito c1 antes del checkout
# Esperado: p1 x2 ($2000) + p2 ($25) = $2025
# Descuento: 10% = $202.50
# Total: $1822.50
GET {{baseUrl}}/cart/{{customerId1}} HTTP/1.1

###

### 86. Checkout Exitoso de c1 (Primera Compra)
# Debe crear una Purchase y vaciar el carrito
# Guardar el purchaseId de la respuesta para tests posteriores
POST {{baseUrl}}/checkout HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId1}}"
}

###

### 87. Verificar que carrito c1 quedó vacío después del checkout
# Esperado: carrito vacío o no encontrado
GET {{baseUrl}}/cart/{{customerId1}} HTTP/1.1

###

### 88. Consultar Historial de Compras de c1
# Debe mostrar la compra recién creada
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases/history/{{customerId1}} HTTP/1.1

###

